			<div class="article-correspondence layout-item fill-pattern-light">
		<div class="layout-item-intro">
			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="500">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>Thank you for publishing Cary Tennis&rsquo;s &ldquo;<a href="/article/4669">Citizens of the Dream</a>&rdquo; [June 2012]. His advice for artists revived my writer&rsquo;s spirit, which has been flagging lately in the face of errands, traffic, expectations, appointments, and fibromyalgia symptoms.</p>

<p>I had two pieces accepted by online magazines this week, but Tennis reminds me that I&rsquo;m writing for myself as well as for publication. Thanks for helping me remember what my dream is really about.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">B. Lynn Goodwin<br>Danville, California</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

								<div class="block-correspondence" id="476">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>Cary Tennis&rsquo;s advice in &ldquo;<a href="/article/4669">Citizens of the Dream</a>&rdquo; [June 2012] is wise and insightful. I&rsquo;m sorry, though, that he still feels a nine-year-old&rsquo;s resentment at his &ldquo;imprisoning&rdquo; classroom in the sixties and at the authoritarian teacher who made the children raise their hands before they spoke and marched up and down the rows in her &ldquo;hard heels.&rdquo;</p>

<p>I feel the need to point out that she was imprisoned too, alone in a room with thirty or more restless children. Her job was to make them sit quietly in an assembly line of seats and desks while she poured measurable quantities of learning into them. She was, no doubt, watched and judged by an authoritarian principal, who was judged by an authoritarian superintendent, who was judged by an authoritarian school board. And they were all judged by grudging taxpayers who assumed that if children didn&rsquo;t measure up, it was the teacher&rsquo;s fault.</p>

<p>That&rsquo;s how it was in most schools back in the sixties, and I&rsquo;m afraid it still is.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Mary Alice Moore<br>King City, Oregon</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

				<div class="text-center">
			<button class="b b-1 xsmall js-b-readmore-correspondence" data-collapsible="#article-correspondences" data-label="Read More Letters">Read More Letters</button>
		</div>
			</div>
    
		<div class="article-correspondence-cta">
		<div class="cta cta-l1" data-url="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">
			<div class="cta-intro">
				<h5 class="cta-title alt-ff">Thinking about writing us a letter?</h5>
				<p class="cta-text">Give in to the temptation. We love getting mail. <br><span class="xsmall">(Of course, we reserve the right to edit.)</span></p>
			</div>
			<a href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor" class="cta-button b b-4 b-padding-tight small" data-label="Write Us A Letter!">Write Us A Letter!</a>
		</div>
	</div>
	

